# Define models for comparison
pos_weight = len(y[y == 0])/len(y[y==1])
class_freqs = [len(y[y == 0]), len(y[y==1])]
class_priors = [1 / freq for freq in class_freqs]
class_weights = [len(y[y == 0])/len(y), len(y[y == 1])/len(y)]



models = {}
models["RandomForest"] = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=16, n_jobs=-1, class_weight="balanced")
models["XGBoost"] = XGBClassifier(random_state=16, eval_metric="mlogloss", gpu_id=0, tree_method="gpu_hist", scale_pos_weight=pos_weight)
models["LGBM"] = LGBMClassifier(random_state=16, class_weight=class_weights)
models["NaiveBayes"] = GaussianNB()
models["AdaBoost"] = AdaBoostClassifier(random_state=16)
models["LogisticRegression"] = Pipeline([("scaler", StandardScaler()), ("logreg", LogisticRegression(random_state=16))])

rf_params = {"n_estimators": [100, 200, 500, 1000],
             "max_depth": [3, 5, 10, 20, 50, None],
             "min_samples_split": [2, 5, 10, 20],
             "class_weight": ["balanced", "balanced_subsample"],
             "min_samples_leaf": [1, 2, 5, 10, 20]
            }

scoring = {"precision": make_scorer(precision_score),
           "recall": make_scorer(recall_score),
           "f1score": make_scorer(f1_score)
          }

rf_rs = RandomizedSearchCV(estimator=models["RandomForest"],
                           param_distributions=rf_params,
                           scoring=scoring,
                           refit="recall",
                           cv=5,
                           n_iter=10,
                           n_jobs=1,
                           verbose=2,
                           random_state=16
                           )

rf_rs.fit(X, y)

best_models["RandomForest"] = rf_rs.best_estimator_
results["RandomForest"] = rf_rs.cv_results_

# combine
model_names = ["RandomForest", "RandomForest_F1", "RandomForest_F4", "XGBoost", "XGBoost_F1", "XGBoost_F4", "LightGBM", "LightGBM_F1", "LightGBM_F4"]
c_reports = [cr_rf, cr_rf_t, cr_rf_f4, cr_xgb, cr_xgb_t, cr_xgb_f4, cr_lgbm, cr_lgbm_t, cr_lgbm_f4]
metrics = ["precision", "recall", "f1-score"]
classes = ["0", "1"]

df_combined = pd.DataFrame()

for model_name, cr in zip(model_names, c_reports):
    for metric in metrics:
        for class_label in classes:
            value = cr[class_label][metric]
            df_combined.loc[f"{metric} - {class_label.split()[-1]}", model_name] = value
